@hostAddress = http://localhost:5184
@auth_token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Authentication API Tests
### Base URL: {{hostAddress}}

### 1. User Login - Admin
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{hostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. User Login - Invalid Credentials
POST {{hostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "invalid",
  "password": "wrong"
}

### 3. Get Current User Info (requires valid JWT token)
### Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with token from login response
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 4. Verify Token (requires valid JWT token)
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/auth/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 5. User Logout (requires valid JWT token)
POST {{hostAddress}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

